<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September 23,
                                        1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. McCormick to ascertain whether a
                                consignment of lumber on the steamer <hi rend="italic">Calchas</hi>
                                has been confiscated or discharged by the Vladivostok prize
                                court.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>